    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*pa(s)nu-ka</w></mentioned>.
        Выпадение %is%i имело место и в сакском; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                    ><lang/><w>phāna-</w><gloss><q>пыль</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>pasnu-</w><gloss><q>пыль</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>прах</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>pam̃su-</w><gloss><q>пыль</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>песок</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Утрата %is%i перед %in%i, как в
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_najyn"/> ‘купать’ из %isnā-%i и <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_nwar"/> из %isnāvar-%i. В случае выпадения носового мы имели бы
        %i*pasuk-%i, чему безупречно отвечает <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
            ><lang/><w>пѣсъкъ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
            ><lang/><w>песок</w></mentioned>. Огласовка %iu%i в д. %ifunuk%i — вторичное явление,
        как в некоторых других случаях (<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
            /><biblScope>368</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>20, 34</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Konow</author><ref
                target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XV 114</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
            ><lang/><w>*pa(s)nu-ka</w></mentioned>. The drop of the %is%i sound happened also in
        Khotanese; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
            ><lang/><w>phāna-</w><gloss><q>dust</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>pasnu-</w><gloss><q>dust</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>ashes</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>pam̃su-</w><gloss><q>dust</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>sand</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The %is%i sound was dropped
        before %in%i as in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_najyn"/> ‘bath’ from %isnā-%i and <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_nwar"/> from %isnāvar-%i. In case of the drop of the nasal
        sound, the form would have looked like %i*pasuk-%i, which is perfectly corresponds with
            <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>пѣсъкъ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><lang/><w>песок</w><gloss><q>sand</q></gloss></mentioned>. The %iu%i voicing in
        Digor %ifunuk%i is a secondary phenomenon, as in some other cases (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>368</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>20, 34</biblScope></bibl>. —
                <bibl><author>Konow</author><ref target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XV
            114</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
